Description: Corroded copper alloy inlay element of oval shape with a flat base and a convex top decorated with longitudinal parallel striations. Lightly patinated with green corrosion.
Curator's comments: The Museum register indicates a general reference to the small bronze finds mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80, but the item is not clearly described.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.81, p.186, pl.28)
